      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:31:4",
      "text": [
        " سَمِعْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) يَقُولُ إِنَّ فِي كِتَابِ عَلِيٍّ ( عليه السلام ) يُضْرَبُ شَارِبُ الْخَمْرِ ثَمَانِينَ وَ شَارِبُ النَّبِيذِ ثَمَانِينَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from hammad Bin Usman, from Bureyd Bin Muawiya who said, ",
          "‘I heard Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> saying that in the Book of Ali<sup>asws</sup>, the drinker of the wine is to be whipped eighty (lashes) and the drinker of <span class=\"iTxt\">Al-Nabeez</span> is to be whipped eighty (lashes)’."
        ]
      }
